# CC PROMPT — v2.24.1 — Fix propose_subtask not called + operation_log writes

## What this does
Three targeted fixes for bugs found in v2.24.0:

(1) RESEARCH_PROMPT was missing the propose_subtask and runbook_search rules —
CC placed them only in ACTION_PROMPT. The investigate agent never sees them so it
never calls propose_subtask after completing an investigation with clear fix steps.

(2) propose_subtask and runbook_search are not in `_ALWAYS_INCLUDE` inside
`rank_tools_for_task`. With top_n=10 and 30+ investigate tools, semantic ranking
silently drops propose_subtask before the model ever sees it.

(3) session_store._flush_loop silently swallows all DB write errors at log.debug
level. asyncpg's handling of SQLAlchemy text() with dict parameters may be failing.
Rewrite the flush to use explicit bindparam() syntax and log errors at ERROR level
so failures are visible, plus add a diagnostic endpoint to verify the table exists
and has rows.

Version bump: 2.24.0 → 2.24.1

